  "title": "Senior Account Executive",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Prepare full set monthly management accounts and related schedules timely</li>\n  <li>Prepare year end statutory report, tax computation, GST reporting, government surveys, audit and reporting.</li>\n  <li>Payment and billing processing</li>\n  <li>Administration of contracts database and project cost tracking</li>\n  <li>Cashflow management, petty cash</li>\n  <li>Participate in the preparation of budget and forecast</li>\n  <li>Liaise with auditors, tax agent, company secretary and bankers</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with Company Policies, Processes and Procedures</li>\n  <li>System and processes- assist in processes and system implementation when required; continue to streamline anPerform daily accounting &amp; finance duties including receivables and parables processes, general ledger, tax and bank reconciliation, etc.;</li>\n  <li>To oversee HR and Account department </li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal skills</li>\n  <li>Teamplayer </li>\n  <li>Details and submit work on time </li>\n  <li>Helping in assest management </li>\n  <li>Prepare monthly financial and management reports;</li>\n  <li>Prepare salary for Monthly staff.</li>\n  <li>Preparation of quarterly GST Returns</li>\n  <li>Handling sub con account/ Back charges</li>\n  <li>Assist in QS to issue invoices. Follow up on Payments.</li>\n  <li>Apply bank facilities when required.</li>\n  <li>Perform Internet banking transactions.</li>\n  <li>Work In progress records.</li>\n  <li>Collection meeting with QS/ Budget Allocation/ Cash Flow meeting and preparation.</li>\n  <li>Consolidate accounts and ensure compliance with accounting standards;</li>\n  <li>Support audit and tax queries;</li>\n  <li>Manage timely closing process and reconciliations, including for inter-company transactions;</li>\n  <li>Preferred Construciton Company Experiences</li>\n  <li>Able to overtime when needed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>*Bachelor’s degree in accounting*</p>",
